'''Form-chair''' was the generic term used to describe any chair which molded itself to the user's body contours.

[[Klo Merit]] had a form-chair in his office at [[Republic Mobile Surgical Unit 7|RMSU-7]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]] was equipped with form-chairs; and [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] also had one, which featured cloned leather and a [[voxchip]] that was not able to pronounce his name.

In [[44 ABY]] after the [[Lost Tribe of Sith emergence]] crisis, the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] was fitted with form-chairs as a suggestion from [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]], after the previous ones were destroyed during the [[Assault on the New Jedi Temple]] by a [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]] thrown by [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentice]] [[Vestara Khai]].<ref name="Apocalypse">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Apocalypse]]''</ref>

